      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "1658ae30a0e97e7f4018d8cba67e459078470d1a",
            "subject": "LU-8130 libcfs: port working hash from upstream"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Alexander Boyko",
          "email": "c17825@cray.com",
          "date": "2018-11-29 08:20:00.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2019-02-11 03:22:11.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-10913 llog: add startcat for wrapped catalog",
        "message": "LU-10913 llog: add startcat for wrapped catalog\n\nThe osp_sync_thread loop for a llog_cat_process has a mistake.\nWhen llog_cat_process has reached a bottom of catalog, the processing\nrestarts with 0. Which means a default processing. In this case a\ncatalog is wrapped and processing starts from a llh_cat_idx. But\nrecords at the bottom were processed already, and were not cancelled\nyet. The next message appears at log.\nosp_sync_interpret()) reply req ffff8800123e3600/1, rc -2, transno 0\n\nllog_cat_process support startcat index for processing catalog.\nIn this case the processing starts from startcat index. But if\ncatalog is wrapped startcat index is ignored.\n\nThe patch adds supporting of startcat index for wrapped catalog.\n\nSigned-off-by: Alexander Boyko <c17825@cray.com>\nChange-Id: Ie4e3ecf2532878578ae0463969115664e3589188\nCray-bug-id: LUS-6765\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/33749\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Sergey Cheremencev <c17829@cray.com>\nReviewed-by: Alexander Zarochentsev <c17826@cray.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
  "requirements": [],
  "submit_records": []
}